  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Wow, a PR so fast? :100: \n\nAbout the way you defined it, I'm just wondering: wouldn't this be the first time we wrap a template inside a subobject of a widget?\n\nI couldn't find any other case of this, correct me if I'm wrong, but for consistency, it might be better to go with `templates.poweredBy`, and then `cssClasses.poweredBy{Root,Link}` or `cssClasses.poweredBy.{root,link}`, no?\n",
    "created_at": "2016-06-01T01:33:30Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/1048#issuecomment-222869235",
    "id": 222869235,
